    "source_note": "No ADI specified - considered safe at all consumption levels. Unlike other sugar alcohols, erythritol is 90% absorbed in the small intestine and excreted unchanged, so it rarely causes digestive issues even at high intakes (50g+). However, some 2023 research suggests potential cardiovascular effects warrant further study."
  },
  "fun_fact": "Erythritol is the 'unicorn' of sugar alcohols - it has almost zero calories, doesn't spike blood sugar, AND doesn't cause the dreaded digestive issues that plague other sugar alcohols! That's because 90% of it gets absorbed before reaching your colon. It's become the darling of the keto diet movement."
